eventRemarks: A pitfall trap was left out for 24 hours, there were 2 pitfall traps in the 4x4m plot placed about 2 feet apart. This collection was a part of an experiment to compare the insect communites on unmanipulated control plots (mostly covered by non-native mustard plants), plots in which native plants were planted and reference plots with intact native chaparral habitat. This was a reference plot. References plots were dominated by Malacothamnus fasciculatus, Salvia leucophylla, and Artemesia californica.

identificationRemarks: to Chalcioidea, ~2mm long, green metallic, wings with stigma right on the marginal vein with a tiny uncus, the postmarginal vein is barely there and about the stize of the stigma, mesosoma bigger the metasoma, lines from the uper corners to the middle of the metanotum, there is a bowtie and the postnotum is football shapped, antenna 13 segmented with 1 annelus, clava not very distinct from the rest of the antennal segments, ocelli are somewhat large, 4-segmented tarsi that are white, two tibial spurs on the mind leg
